description:
Lines 128-136, 232-239, 282-289, 299-306, 331-338, 345-352, 406-413, 488-495 all have identical JSON deserialization boilerplate:

    let params: SomeType = match serde_json::from_value(
        notif.params.unwrap_or(serde_json::Value::Null),
    ) {
        Ok(p) => p,
        Err(e) => {
            tracing::warn!("{context}_parse error: {e}");
            return Ok(());
        }
    };

This pattern appears 8 times. Extract:

fn parse_message_params<T: Deserialize>(value: Option<Value>, context: &str) -> Option<T> {
    match serde_json::from_value(value.unwrap_or(Value::Null)) {
        Ok(p) => Some(p),
        Err(e) => {
            tracing::warn!("{context} parse error: {e}");
            None
        }
    }
}

Then replace all 8 sites with:
if let Some(params) = parse_message_params::<DirectoryListParams>(..., "directory_list") { ... }

Benefits:
- Eliminates boilerplate noise
- Standardizes error handling
- Single place to change parsing strategy
